  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed operating points. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; required and achieved levels are documented. Decision: Accepted based on documented evidence packages. Note: the context of use description enumerates temperature (35–38 °C), inlet pressure (5–15 mmHg), outlet pressure (60–120 mmHg), and flow regime (laminar-to-transitional, Re 200–2400) as narrative — no structured hasOperatingEnvelope or hasApplicabilityConstraint is linked, leaving the formal boundary of model validity unspecified.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-piv-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-experimental-2021"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "type": "ContextOfUse",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). The device operates with blood temperature in the physiological range of 35–38 °C, inlet gauge pressures of 5–15 mmHg, outlet gauge pressures of 60–120 mmHg, and flow rates of 3–6 L/min at rotational speeds of 2400–3200 RPM. Flow regime spans laminar to low-transitional (Reynolds numbers 200–2400 in critical gap regions). Blood viscosity is modeled as non-Newtonian (Carreau-Yasuda) with hematocrit 35–45%. These ranges are described here for context; model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "decisionConsequence": "High"
  },
